    dc:date "2020" ;
    dc:title "Modern taxonomic approaches to identifying diatrypaceous fungi from marine habitats, with a novel genus Halocryptovalsa Dayarathne & K. D. Hyde, gen. nov." ;
    fabio:hasPart <http://dx.doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.7815059>, <http://dx.doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.7815061>, <http://dx.doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.7815044>, <http://dx.doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.7815048> ;
    a fabio:JournalArticle .

<http://dx.doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.7815059>
    dc:description "FIG. 5. — Sexual morph of Cryptosphaeria avicenniae Devadatha & V.V.Sarma, sp. nov. (AMH-9952 – holotype): A, ascomata erumpent, immersed in decaying wood of Avicennia marina; B, horizontal sections of ascomata; C, vertical section of ascomata; D, peridium; E-I, immature and mature asci; J, paraphyses; K-O, ascospores; P, germ tube develop from apical side of ascospore; Q, R, culture on PDA (Q-upper, R-lower). Scale bars: C, 100 μm; D, E, 50 μm; F-I, J, K = 20 μm; J, K, 20 μm; L-P, 5 μm." ;
    fabio:hasRepresentation "https://zenodo.org/record/7815059/files/figure.png" ;
    a fabio:Figure .

<http://dx.doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.7815061>
    dc:description "FIG. 6. — Asexual morph of Cryptosphaeria avicenniae Devadatha & V.V.Sarma, sp. nov. (AMH-9952 – holotype): A, conidiomata on host (Avicennia marina); B, C, horizontal section through conidioma;D, peridium;E, F, conidiophores and conidiogenous cells;G-L, conidia.Scale bars:B-C,100 μm;D, 50 μm; E-L,10 μm." ;
    fabio:hasRepresentation "https://zenodo.org/record/7815061/files/figure.png" ;
    a fabio:Figure .

<http://dx.doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.7815044>
    dc:description "FIG. 1. — Phylogram generated from the best scoring RAxML tree based on combined ITS and Btub sequence data. Bootstrap support values for maximum likelihood (ML,black) and maximum parsimony (MP, blue) equal or greater than 60 % are given above the nodes. Bayesian posterior probabilities (PP,green) equal or greater than 0.90 are shown above the branch. The tree is rooted to Xylaria hypoxylon (CBS 122620) and Kretzschmaria deusta (CBS 826.72). All sequences from ex-type strains are in bold. Symbols:, polysporous species;, octosporous species;, species with less than eight spores. Scale bar: 0.2 (expected number of nucleotide substitutions per site per branch)." ;
    fabio:hasRepresentation "https://zenodo.org/record/7815044/files/figure.png" ;
    a fabio:Figure .

<http://dx.doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.7815048>
    dc:description "FIG. 2. — Phylogram generated from the best scoring RAxML tree based on ITS sequence data. Bootstrap support values for maximum likelihood (ML, black) and maximum parsimony (MP, blue) equal or greater than 60% are given above the nodes. Bayesian posterior probabilities (PP,green) equal or greater than 0.90 are shown above the branch. The tree is rooted to Xylaria hypoxylon (CBS 122620) and Kretzschmaria deusta (CBS 826.72). Scale bar: 0.09 (expected number of nucleotide substitutions per site per branch)." ;
    fabio:hasRepresentation "https://zenodo.org/record/7815048/files/figure.png" ;
    a fabio:Figure .

